abstract: The New Hampshire primary and Nevada caucuses have passed, and South Carolina’s vote is just days away — but there’s still no winner of the Iowa caucuses.
snippet: The New Hampshire primary and Nevada caucuses have passed, and South Carolina’s vote is just days away — but there’s still no winner of the Iowa caucuses.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The New Hampshire primary and Nevada caucuses have passed, and South Carolina’s vote is just days away — but there’s still no winner of the Iowa caucuses.
headline_main: AP Explains: Why There Isn't a Winner of Iowa's Dem Caucuses
headline_print_headline: AP Explains: Why There Isn't a Winner of Iowa's Dem Caucuses

abstract: The Trump team confirms all of our worst fears.
snippet: The Trump team confirms all of our worst fears.
lead_paragraph: So, here’s the response of the Trump team and its allies to the coronavirus, at least so far: It’s actually good for America. Also, it’s a hoax perpetrated by the news media and the Democrats. Besides, it’s no big deal, and people should buy stocks. Anyway, we’ll get it all under control under the leadership of a man who doesn’t believe in science.

headline_main: When a Pandemic Meets a Personality Cult
headline_print_headline: Pandemic, Meet the Trump Personality Cult

abstract: At a closed-door meeting, Speaker Nancy Pelosi urged Democrats to “keep our eye on the ball” and mocked President Trump’s skin color: “The ball has an orange face.”
snippet: At a closed-door meeting, Speaker Nancy Pelosi urged Democrats to “keep our eye on the ball” and mocked President Trump’s skin color: “The ball has an orange face.”
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Speaker Nancy Pelosi, facing deep alarm among moderate Democrats who worry that Senator Bernie Sanders will win their party’s presidential nomination only to cost them control of the House, has begun distancing her caucus from the race for the White House in an effort to insulate her rank and file and preserve the party’s majority.

abstract: And many of them tell us they’re willing to use a brokered convention to stop Bernie Sanders.

lead_paragraph: Hi. Welcome to On Politics, your guide to the day in national politics. I’m Lisa Lerer, your host, writing to you aboard a flight to Texas, one of the states voting next week on Super Tuesday.

abstract: The risk to American people from coronavirus is low, but that could change, U.S. Health and Human Services Secretary Alex Azar said on Thursday.
snippet: The risk to American people from coronavirus is low, but that could change, U.S. Health and Human Services Secretary Alex Azar said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The risk to American people from coronavirus is low, but that could change, U.S. Health and Human Services Secretary Alex Azar said on Thursday.
headline_main: Coronavirus Risk to Americans Low, but That Can Change: U.S. Health Secretary
headline_print_headline: Coronavirus Risk to Americans Low, but That Can Change: U.S. Health Secretary

abstract: President Donald Trump may not divert $89 million intended for a military construction project in Washington state to build his border wall, a U.S. judge in Seattle ruled Thursday.
snippet: President Donald Trump may not divert $89 million intended for a military construction project in Washington state to build his border wall, a U.S. judge in Seattle ruled Thursday.
lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — President Donald Trump may not divert $89 million intended for a military construction project in Washington state to build his border wall, a U.S. judge in Seattle ruled Thursday.
headline_main: Judge: Military Funds for Washington State Can't Go to Wall
headline_print_headline: Judge: Military Funds for Washington State Can't Go to Wall

abstract: Cherokee citizens are calling on Elizabeth Warren to publicly disavow a family story of indigenous heritage as a way to dissuade others from making false claims they say often romanticize Native Americans.
snippet: Cherokee citizens are calling on Elizabeth Warren to publicly disavow a family story of indigenous heritage as a way to dissuade others from making false claims they say often romanticize Native Americans.
lead_paragraph: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. — Cherokee citizens are calling on Elizabeth Warren to publicly disavow a family story of indigenous heritage as a way to dissuade others from making false claims they say often romanticize Native Americans.
headline_main: Warren Still Dogged by Past Claims of Indigenous Ancestry
headline_print_headline: Warren Still Dogged by Past Claims of Indigenous Ancestry

abstract: He is not a liberal, he’s the end of liberalism.
snippet: He is not a liberal, he’s the end of liberalism.
lead_paragraph: A few months ago, I wrote a column saying I would vote for Elizabeth Warren over Donald Trump. I may not agree with some of her policies, but culture is more important than politics. She does not spread moral rot the way Trump does.

abstract: The Trump administration moved Thursday on a water-recycling push it says could get good use out of more of the wastewater that industries, cities and farms spew out, including the billions of barrels of watery waste generated by oil and gas fields each year.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration moved Thursday on a water-recycling push it says could get good use out of more of the wastewater that industries, cities and farms spew out, including the billions of barrels of watery waste generated by oil and gas fields each year.
headline_main: US Considers More Water Recycling _ Including From Oilfields
headline_print_headline: US Considers More Water Recycling _ Including From Oilfields
